âœ…âœ…system booting issues:
If a system is not booting, first I check the power connection, cables, and display. 
Then I verify the hardware components like SMPS, RAM and hard disk are properly connected. 
I check BIOS settings and boot order, and if the system powers on but OS doesnâ€™t load, I perform startup repair or use Safe Mode. If itâ€™s a hardware issue, I replace or escalate it to the concerned team.

âœ…âœ…If a laptop or desktop is not turning on,
Â I first check the power source, power cable, and adapter connection. 
 Then I check the battery or SMPS, and verify if any lights or fan activity is present. 
 I also reseat the RAM and power cables, and test with another power source. 
 If thereâ€™s still no response, I suspect a hardware issue like motherboard or power supply failure and escalate it to the hardware team.

1.âœ…âœ… No Power / Not Turning On
Causes: Faulty adapter, loose power cable, drained battery, motherboard issue.
Troubleshooting:
Check power cable & adapter.
Try hard reset (remove battery + hold power button).
Test with another charger.
Check power LED / charger LED.
If still dead â†’ possible motherboard or DC jack failure.

2.âœ…âœ… Laptop Battery Not Charging / Draining Fast
Causes: Faulty adapter, dead battery cells, charging IC issue, background apps.
Troubleshooting:
Try different charger.
Check battery health in BIOS/Windows.
Disable unnecessary apps, reduce brightness.
Calibrate battery.
Replace battery if swollen/weak.

3.âœ…âœ… Overheating / Fan Noise
Causes: Dust in vents, thermal paste dried, heavy usage, fan failure.
Troubleshooting:
Clean fans.
remove dust.
Reapply thermal paste.
Ensure proper airflow.
Check running apps in Task Manager.
Replace faulty fan.

4.âœ…âœ… Blue Screen of Death (BSOD)
Causes: Driver issues, RAM/HDD failure, overheating, system file corruption.
Troubleshooting:
Note the stop code.
Update/reinstall drivers.
Run Memory Diagnostic, SFC/DISM.
Replace faulty RAM/HDD.
Check for overheating.

5.âœ…âœ… Slow Performance / System Hang
Causes: Low RAM, HDD failure, too many startup programs, malware.
Troubleshooting:
Disable startup apps.
Clean temp file
Upgrade to SSD.
Scan for virus.
Increase RAM.

6.âœ…âœ… Keyboard Keys Not Working
Causes: Dust, driver issue, liquid damage, cable loose.
Troubleshooting:
Test with external keyboard.
Reinstall keyboard driver.
Clean keys.
Reseat keyboard connector (for laptops).
Replace keyboard if damaged.

7.âœ…âœ… Touchpad Not Working

Causes: Disabled touchpad, driver corruption, hardware issue.
Troubleshooting:
Enable touchpad (Fn + key).
Update/reinstall driver.
Check touchpad settings.
Reseat/replace touchpad module.

8.âœ…âœ… Screen Flickering / No Display / Lines on Screen

Causes: Loose display cable, GPU failure, LCD issue.
Troubleshooting:
Connect to external monitor (check GPU).
Reseat/replace display cable (LVDS/eDP).
Update graphics drivers.
Replace screen if damaged.

9.âœ…âœ… Broken Hinges / Damaged Ports (USB/HDMI)

Causes: Physical damage, wear & tear.
Troubleshooting:
Replace hinges/frame.
Replace USB/HDMI port or entire I/O board.
For minor cracks â†’ use hinge reinforcement kit.

10.âœ…âœ… Hard Disk Failure / SSD Failure

Causes: Bad sectors, old drive, overheating, power surges.
Troubleshooting:
Run SMART test.
Use CHKDSK for temporary fix.
Backup data immediately.
Replace HDD/SSD.
Reinstall OS.

11.âœ…âœ… RAM Issues (Beeping Sound / Random Reboot)

Causes: Faulty RAM stick, loose RAM, incompatibility.
Troubleshooting:

Reseat RAM.
Test RAM sticks one by one.
Run Memory Diagnostic.
Replace faulty RAM stick.

12.âœ…âœ… Wi-Fi Button/Adapter Not Detected

Causes: Disabled adapter, driver issue, airplane mode, hardware failure.
Troubleshooting:
Enable Wi-Fi adapter in Device Manager.
Reinstall Wi-Fi drivers.
Turn off Airplane mode.
Reset network settings.
Replace Wi-Fi card if not detected.















